Content Licensing Notes:

- Prayer texts (Our Father, Hail Mary, Glory Be, etc.) are in the public domain.
- The Rule of St. Francis (1223) is in the public domain.
- Stations of the Cross meditations are original compositions or public domain.
- Franciscan Crown Rosary mysteries are based on traditional Franciscan sources.
- Saint quotes are attributed to their original authors and are in the public domain.
- Liturgical calendar data provided by LitCal API (John Romano D'Orazio).
- Daily Mass readings linked from USCCB (United States Conference of Catholic Bishops).
- Liturgy of the Hours linked from DivineOffice.org.
- Examination of Conscience questions are based on traditional Franciscan sources.
